@node "what" "What is The X-0-X Package?"

@{JCENTER}@{b}@{u}What is The X-0-X Package?@{ub}@{uu}

The X-0-X Package is a complete set of 'editors' for the Roland
@{"TB303" link "TB303" 0}, @{"TR606" link "TR606" 0}, @{"TR707" link "TR707" 0}, @{"TR808" link "TR808" 0} & @{"TR909" link "TR909" 0 }.
You can use the editors to 'copy' the data that's on your TB or TR and save it on your HD.
Now if the batteries are dead or you want to clean some banks (you might need them),
you still have the banks stored on your HD. These editors have the same simple
interface as each other and they should work like the real machines.
But, they don't play the music for you... :-(

@endnode

@node "req" "Requirements"

@{JCENTER}@{b}@{u}Requirements@{ub}@{uu}

What you need: An Amiga, KS 2.04+, asl.library, gadtools.library & @{b}gtlayout.library V41+@{ub} 
What's also @{u}needed@{uu} is a TB303, TR606, 707, 808 or 909. Why ? Well you have to get the data from them...

@endnode

@node "usage" "Usage"

@{JCENTER}@{b}@{u}Usage@{ub}@{uu}

It's very simple to use. Just put the real machine on and start the program with the
same name. Now just do the same thing on the machine as on the program. That's
selecting a bank(Pattern Write ofcourse) and press start/stop. Now select
the instrument you want. Look at the machine and see what steps are selected.
Simply press the according buttons on the program. If you want to switch to
another bank press start/stop again and select another bank. Just like a real one.
You don't have to press start/stop again, if you want to change the Instrument,
Part or Basic-Variation. If you're done, select Menu/SaveAs.

@{JCENTER}@{b}Keys@{ub}

The 'S' key for Start/Stop. I/Shift I/Down & Up Arrow keys: for selecting next/prev.
Instrument. Right & Left Arrow keys: to move to the next/prev. bank.
B/Shift B for selecting A or B Basic-Variation. P/Shift P for selecting
1st or 2nd Part. 1 to 0 to select a bank(1-10), when Start/Stop is off. 
When Start/Stop is on, 1 to 0 presses a note.

With the TR-editors, switching the parts/bvar/instruments/banks can be done at
any(!)time, whether the start-stop button is pressed or not.

@{JCENTER}@{b}Note@{ub}

@{u}Basic-Variation & Parts is only on the 808Editor, because only the TR808 have them.@{uu}


@endnode

